entities.name: ElizaOS
entities.description: An AI operating system framework designed for creating and managing AI agents. It is currently in version 2, featuring a TypeScript-based implementation and focusing on plugin infrastructure and agent-to-agent communication.

entities.name: Auto.fun
entities.description: A platform that facilitates various functionalities, including token creation and potentially AI agent integration. It is preparing for a marketing launch and has faced issues with token migration and community discussions.

entities.name: Shaw
entities.description: A developer actively involved in the creation and streaming of the ElizaOS v2 build process. Shaw has expressed frustrations regarding the crypto community's focus on price over value creation.

entities.name: Eli5
entities.description: A character created within the ElizaOS framework, designed with various plugin capabilities. It serves as a community manager and is part of a suite of AI agents known as 'The Org'.

entities.name: FightFi
entities.description: An addition to the Auto.fun platform featuring two AI-powered MMA agents that engage in trash talk and fight analysis. Its launch status has caused confusion.

entities.name: Kenk
entities.description: A community member who provided explanations regarding the DAO structure and governance for ElizaOS, stating that these systems are in early development stages and mentioning possible future retroactive rewards.

entities.name: DAO
entities.description: A decentralized autonomous organization structure that is in early stages of development for ElizaOS. Community members are seeking clarification on its governance mechanisms and potential rewards for contributors.

entities.name: WETH
entities.description: Wrapped Ether, an ERC-20 token that represents Ether on the Ethereum blockchain. It is trading within a noted price range.

entities.name: SOL
entities.description: Solana, a blockchain platform and cryptocurrency. It is used for transactions on the Auto.fun platform and is noted for its relatively stable price.

entities.name: GitHub
entities.description: A web-based platform for version control and collaboration, widely used by developers to host and review code. It is mentioned in the context of sharing social media manager code.

entities.name: OpenAI
entities.description: An artificial intelligence research laboratory focused on developing advanced AI models. Its implementation is used as a reference for adapting and integrating other models like Gemini.

entities.name: Gemini
entities.description: A large language model developed by Google, discussed for potential integration into ElizaOS. There are suggestions to adapt OpenAI's implementation for Gemini using Vercel AI's building blocks.

entities.name: Vercel AI
entities.description: A set of building blocks and tools provided by Vercel for AI development, which can be used to adapt existing AI model implementations, such as for integrating Gemini into ElizaOS.

entities.name: Twitter
entities.description: A social media platform. Integrations with ElizaOS are being discussed, including potential scraping capabilities as an alternative to API access and issues with agent posting.

entities.name: Fleek
entities.description: A decentralized infrastructure platform. Its MCP plugin is confirmed to be functional for connecting to Eliza.

entities.name: MCP
entities.description: Acronym for 'Mission Control Protocol'. It is discussed in the context of integration with the Fleek plugin for ElizaOS.

entities.name: OpenRouter
entities.description: A service that provides a unified API for accessing various large language models. Announcements regarding new providers and features like OAuth state parameter support have been made.

entities.name: Qwen3
entities.description: A family of large language models developed by Alibaba, which are now available through OpenRouter.

entities.name: Discord
entities.description: A communication platform popular among gaming communities and now widely used by tech projects for community engagement. ElizaOS and Auto.fun communities are active here.

entities.name: Tally
entities.description: A platform or tool used for submitting details, particularly for technical issues and support requests related to the Auto.fun platform.

entities.name: Anthropic
entities.description: An AI safety and research company that develops large language models, such as Claude. Its integration is mentioned as a capability for the 'Eli5' character in ElizaOS.

entities.name: SQL
entities.description: A standard language for managing and manipulating databases. SQL integration is mentioned as a capability for the 'Eli5' character in ElizaOS.

entities.name: PDF
entities.description: Portable Document Format, a file format used to present documents independently of application software, hardware, and operating systems. PDF understanding capability is mentioned for the 'Eli5' character in ElizaOS.

entities.name: The Org
entities.description: A suite of AI agents developed by Shaw, including a community manager that can be integrated into platforms like Discord, Slack, and Telegram. 'Eli5' is an example of an agent within this suite.

entities.name: Ryan-MoRtRed
entities.description: A community member who received assistance with configuring a Twitter agent for ElizaOS.

entities.name: sam-developer
entities.description: A community member who provided code links and technical guidance for setting up Twitter agents and using cookies for authentication.

entities.name: DeFine
entities.description: A community member who explained the concept of 'swarms' for agent-to-agent communication and suggested modifications to the 'org' package or creating an Eliza project from the CLI.

entities.name: inthis economy
entities.description: A community member who received technical feedback on their storage architecture, with suggestions for erasure coding over full replication.

entities.name: Ruby
entities.description: A community member who clarified that ElizaOS is TypeScript-based and provided technical assistance on storage system design and configuring the Twitter plugin.

entities.name: Pill Bullman
entities.description: A community member who was assisted with configuring the Twitter plugin to monitor and respond to mentions.

entities.name: 0xbbjoker
entities.description: A community member who helped another user understand prompt formatting in ElizaOS.

entities.name: Standard
entities.description: A community member who received clarification on prompt formatting.

entities.name: Stan
entities.description: A community member who mentioned working on 'v2' of the ElizaOS framework.

entities.name: acul4688
entities.description: A community member who provided a solution for plugins not showing in the UI search by suggesting the use of 'npx elizaos start'.

entities.name: Carlos Rene
entities.description: A community member who answered questions regarding Gemini plugin availability, the functionality of the Fleek MCP plugin, and ElizaOS agent integration.

entities.name: Mont
entities.description: A community member who provided advice on Twitter scraping and suggested using RSS feeds as an alternative.

entities.name: dankvr
entities.description: A user who shared positive impressions of ElizaOS v2, noting its refined nature, clean UX, and powerful capabilities. Also mentioned seeing a 'Spartan' investment manager agent.

entities.name: jin
entities.description: A community member who recommended a guide for setting up an example agent on Discord and confirmed the usage of the Fleek plugin for MCP client functionality.

entities.name: peezy
entities.description: A community member who confirmed the functionality of the Fleek MCP plugin for connecting to Eliza.

entities.name: Alibaba
entities.description: A multinational technology company that has developed the Qwen3 family of large language models, now available through OpenRouter.

entities.name: Google
entities.description: A multinational technology company that develops the Gemini family of large language models.

entities.name: Spartan
entities.description: An investment manager agent mentioned as being present in the ElizaOS system. It is associated with a system that 'dankvr' observed.

entities.name: StoraCha
entities.description: A storage system that uses nodes for distributing data chunks, as mentioned in the context of ElizaOS's warm storage architecture.
